# AI Governance

## Ownership

- This codebase is **100% AI-maintained**. Implement, refactor, document, and changelog all changes via AI.
- The human user directs work in Korean chat only.

## Language

- **User replies**: Korean only.
- **Code, comments, docs, rules, changelog, handover**: English only.
- **In-app UI**: Korean via `tr()` / `QStringLiteral`. Keep JSON block `type` values in English.

## After Every Completed Task

1. Append entries under `[Unreleased]` in **AGENTS.md** section **11. Changelog and Version History** as you implement.
2. **Immediate handover (same task):** If work touches git/GitHub, release/deploy, scripts agents run, repo URLs, build/CI policy, or user phrase workflows — update the **relevant AGENTS.md section** (e.g. §3.6, §8) **in the same task**, not changelog-only. See `.cursor/rules/immediate-handover.mdc`.
3. **Before closing the task:** bump version per **AGENTS.md** §10 — update `CMakeLists.txt`, move `[Unreleased]` into `## [x.y.z] - YYYY-MM-DD`, leave empty `[Unreleased]`. **Do not** run `cmake --build` at task close unless the user explicitly asks. Static `dist/SuckbongMachine.exe` **only when the user explicitly requests** distribution. **Never** finish with changelog-only `[Unreleased]` entries and the same version number.
4. Keep diffs minimal; match existing C++ / Qt conventions in surrounding code.

